Four inmates of the Maximum Correctional Centre in Jos, Plateau State have escaped from the facility, The PUNCH learnt on Thursday. The correctional centre said to be housing thousands of inmates is located near the State Police Command headquarters in the state capital. A staff of the correctional facility told our correspondent that the four inmates escaped in the early hours of Thursday. The source said, “It was in the night that the incident happened. But how the inmates were able to beat the security and escaped is what some of us don’t understand.” The spokesman of the correctional centre, Mr Geoffrey Longdien confirmed the escape of the four inmates Longdien said, “Four inmates of the correctional centre escaped at the early hours of Thursday. Investigation is ongoing and we shall brief the press when we finish.”